(* Error test 16 — affine variable captured by a closure (Phase 9 hardening).
   Expected: type error — g captures the affine io token, and a closure may
   be called any number of times: g(1) and g(2) would each hand back the
   *same* IO resource, duplicating it without the name ever appearing twice
   in the outer scope.  The affine tracker counts uses per scope, so before
   this check the program was accepted — an affine soundness hole found by
   the Phase 9 hardening review.  Closures must receive affine values as
   parameters, never by capture. *)

module AffineCapture

fn f(io : IO) : (IO, IO) =
  let g = fn(x : Int) => io in
  (g(1), g(2))
